      "SummaryText": "The Risk Management Plan review was completed June 24, 2009.  The TOTAL Petrochemicals U.S.A. Refinery utilizes an effective integrated safety management system to identify, evaluate, and eliminate or greatly reduce the possibility of an accidental negative event. The site refines oil to produce gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, and petrochemicals to be used as building blocks for other products, and complies with OSHA, EPA, State and local regulations.  There have been no offsite accidental releases the past five years, that has impacted the surrounding community.  Emergency response is handled by refinery employees who are well trained in emergency reponse activities.  If needed, the site also a member of the Sabine Neches Chiefs Mutual Aid Association.   The updates since the last submission include a facility name change to TOTAL Petrochemicals U.S.A. Inc., the parent company name change to Total, parent company Duns number to 275137164.  Also the responsible person for the RMP has changed to Charles Kosh.  The Refinery has added Safer Systems monitors around the perimeter of the facility.  The revalidation of PHA's and updating of training is an ongoing process."
